      "content": "The right way is a very difficult balancing act, as religious freedom and secular equality are often in direct conflict. Allowing broad religious exemptions to laws like healthcare or anti-discrimination protections fundamentally undermines the principle of equal protection under the law for all citizens. A secular government must strive to uphold universal rights, meaning exemptions should be extremely narrow and narrowly tailored to avoid creating exceptions that favor one belief system over others.",
