      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The concept of a secular government is not about suppressing conscience; it is about ensuring that the state itself remains neutral and does not endorse any specific religion. When religious exemptions are allowed to override fundamental civil rights, the state is effectively endorsing one religious viewpoint over the rights of others. Therefore, the commitment to universal, secular equality must take precedence because it protects the rights of *everyone*, regardless of their beliefs.",
      "source": "target",
