      "content": "The core function of a modern, functioning society is to ensure that all citizens can participate in the public sphere without being discriminated against based on protected characteristics. While religious freedom is a vital liberty, it cannot be used as a shield to violate the equally fundamental civil rights of others. The state's duty to prevent harm and ensure equality for all citizens is the ultimate, non-negotiable foundation of a just society.",
      "source": "target",
